@zeertzjq 
> The stacktrace doesn't seem to contain any useful information. Can you obtain a backtrace using a Debug build?

Thanks for the reply, haven't done this before, what are the concrete steps to do it?

In my case, the crash is caused by [nvim-cmp](https://github.com/hrsh7th/nvim-cmp) cmdline completion. When editing in cmdline, nvim exits abruptly from time to time.
```
cmp.setup.cmdline(':', {
    mapping = cmp.mapping.preset.cmdline(),
    sources = cmp.config.sources({
      { name = 'path' }
    }, {
      { name = 'cmdline' }
    })
  })
```

@xuyangy thanks, I'll keep an eye on that since I have the same configuration for cmdline too "by chance":
```lua
    -- Use cmdline & path source for ':' (if you enabled `native_menu`, this won't work anymore).
    cmp.setup.cmdline(":", {
      mapping = cmp.mapping.preset.cmdline(),
      sources = cmp.config.sources(
      {
        { name = "path" },
      },
      {
        {
          name = "cmdline",
          -- option = {
          --   ignore_cmds = { 'Man', '!' }
          -- }
        },
      }),
```
